<br>
My view: <br>
<br>
When I started on vazaelle about 2 years ago and made a chanter I would wonder around zones selling wis and int rings and such for 2x cost. took time but made a worth wild profit. Every since Luclin and the bazaar you seem to be lucky to get even 5pp + costs for an item made. IE Valorium rings I am now sitting on them because the best best in bazaar is sometimes only 2k over what I pay for the raw materials. Hi end stuff usually costs 3/4 the cost of the finished product.... I kinda feel the skill, aside from helping my guild and friends, was a waste of time.... I have even seen Resist gear selling as cheap if not cheaper than a single gem used in its creation. I kinda feel cheated from the bazaar. Although its a great place to sell everything, I just wanted to know if other tradeskillers were disappointed in the selling gains vs. material costs?<br>
<br>
PS another thing that this noob was a bit flustered over : When you equip and item ( in a given slot) you get its bonuses, I was looking forward to my GM item in my ammo slot for extra stat boost.... Nope SOE to NoOB central ... you dont get bonuses from ammo slot .... /rude soe ! <br>
