<br>
1) I don't feel tradeskills are a waste of time.  They're not always a moneypit... but there IS money to be made.<br>
<br>
However, I think its funny when people start doing tradeskills to make 'phat plat' and never see it happen.  When people ask me 'how do I make money' guess what I tell them?  I tell them to farm things that tradeskillers want, and sell it too them.  Leather Paddings, swirling shadows, essence of sunlight, silk swatches, etc etc etc.  There is MONEY to be made there.<br>
<br>
2) I don't feel tradeskills are useless.  Prices on stuff like Valorium Rings and Tae Ew Shields have DROPPED because they're so easy to make (not a lot of rare components, success rate fairly good).  This DOES make them harder to sell, however when you're the first person into a particlar market, there is a LOT of money to be made there.<br>
<br>
As more people GM each of the tradeskills, there is more and more stuff entering the bazaar.  As such, people drop their prices in order to move product.  <br>
<br>
3) Does the bazaar cheat you?  I don't feel so.  Its simple supply and demand.  CERTAIN people will ALWAYS try to cheat you, but I feel the bazaar system in of itself is very fair.  It lets a single person see EVERYTHING that everyone is selling and find the best price at any particlar moment.  Meanwhile it lets sellers set up, instead of trying to sit in EC again, trying to move product.  <br>
<br>
<br>
I smith.  I help my guild with my skill every oppurtunity I get.  But I also use my skill to make minor profit for myself.  <br>
<br>
One suggestion Magik, instead of making things that are already in mass in the bazaar... take orders.  Have someone bring you components and charge for combine.  Charge people if they're missing pieces, and take them out of your 'personal stash'.  That way you avoid the bazaar all together, and don't sit on product that you made and can't sell.  It make be a slow business, but at least you have cash in hand.<br>
<br>
